    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140\"><html>\n\n<head>\n \n\n\n \n \n \n \n \n\n<style>\n<!--\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140  \n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1108286140 {font-family:Tahoma;panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140  \n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 p.ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal, #ygrps-yiv-1108286140 li.ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal, #ygrps-yiv-1108286140 div.ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:12.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 a:link, #ygrps-yiv-1108286140 span.ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoHyperlink\n\t{color:blue;text-decoration:underline;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 a:visited, #ygrps-yiv-1108286140 span.ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{color:blue;text-decoration:underline;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 tt\n\t{font-family:\"Courier New\";}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 span.ygrps-yiv-1108286140EmailStyle18\n\t{font-family:Arial;color:navy;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 span.ygrps-yiv-1108286140SpellE\n\t{}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 span.ygrps-yiv-1108286140GramE\n\t{}\n _filtered #ygrps-yiv-1108286140 {margin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in;}\n#ygrps-yiv-1108286140 div.ygrps-yiv-1108286140Section1\n\t{}\n-->\n</style>\n\n</head>\n\n \n\n<div class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140Section1\">\n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>That isn&#8217;t the problem.<span\n style=''>&nbsp; </span>The exception IS being thrown, but <span\n class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140SpellE\">JUnit</span> isn&#8217;t catching it so it is killing <span\n class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140SpellE\">JUnit</span>.<span style=''>&nbsp; </span></span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>Theodore I will look into what you are\nsuggesting.<span style=''>&nbsp; </span>I actually have already\nfound a work around, but I am <span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140GramE\">know</span> more interested in\nunderstanding what was causing the problem for further use.<span\n style=''>&nbsp; </span></span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'>Thanks</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\"><font size=\"2\" color=\"navy\" face=\"Arial\"><span style='\nfont-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\" style='margin-left:.5in;'><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Tahoma;'>-----Original Message-----<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>From:</span></b> Eric Heikkila [mailto:ericheikkila@...]\n<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>Sent:</span></b> Monday, March 18, 2002 8:14\nPM<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>To:</span></b> junit@yahoogroups.com<br>\n<b><span style='font-weight:bold;'>Subject:</span></b> Re: [junit] Re: Get\nAssertionFailedError when assert from another thread.</span></font></p>\n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\" style='margin-left:.5in;'><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\"><span\n style='font-size:12.0pt;'> &nbsp;</span></font></p> \n\n<p class=\"ygrps-yiv-1108286140MsoNormal\" style='margin-left:.5in;'><tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;'>hmmm...there is information about that in the FAQ from</span></font></tt><font\n size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">the www.junit.org website.&nbsp; Usually when I&#39;m\ntesting</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">that an exception is supposed to be thrown, I&#39;ll\ndo</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">something like:</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">public void testExceptionThrown() {</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp; try {</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMyClass.methodThatThrows();</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fail(&quot;Should\nhave thrown MyClassException&quot;);</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp; } catch (MyClassException\nmyClassException) {</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&nbsp;&nbsp; }</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">}</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">The website mentions that, and also an exception\ntest</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">case, but I haven&#39;t used that yet.</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">-Eric</font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">--- nsparis &lt;nathan.paris@...&gt;\nwrote:</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; Let me make it clearer...The exception is\nthrown,</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; which is what is </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; suppose to happen, but instead of being\nprinted out</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; in JUnit it </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; crashes JUnit.&nbsp; I.e. JUnit isnt\nautomatically</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; catching it and </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; flagging it as an error for the test\ncase.&nbsp; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; What do I need to change so that JUnit\ncatches the</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; exception and </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; reports it as an error?</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; --- In junit@y..., &quot;nsparis&quot;\n&lt;nathan.paris@l...&gt;</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; wrote:</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; In one of my tests I start a thread that\nwill call</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; update() when it </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; is done.&nbsp; In the Update I check the\nresults.&nbsp;&nbsp; If</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; an </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; assert it called because something isnt\ncorrect, I</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; get the </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; Exception:</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; junit.framework.AssertionFailedError:\n&quot;Message I</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; had in the assert </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; stmt.&quot;</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; Is there something different I need to\ndo when I</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; am running threads </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; in my tests?</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; &gt; Thanks</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; </font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">&gt; </font></tt><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">__________________________________________________</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Do You Yahoo!?</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">Yahoo! Sports - live college hoops coverage</font></tt><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sports.yahoo.com/\">http://sports.yahoo.com/</a></font></tt><br>\n</span></font><br style=''>\n<br style=''>\n</p> \n\n<tt><font size=\"2\"\n face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>To unsubscribe from this\ngroup, send an email to:</span></font></tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span\n style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\"Courier New\";'><br>\n<tt><font face=\"Courier New\">junit-unsubscribe@yahoogroups.com</font></tt><br>\n</span></font><br>\n<br>\n<tt><font size=\"2\" face=\"Courier New\"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Your use of\nYahoo! Groups is subject to the <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://docs.yahoo.com/info/terms/\">Yahoo!\nTerms of Service</a>.</span></font></tt> \n\n</div>\n\n \n\n</html></div>", 
